                                        lines. On the fragment, 7 lines survive on the recto and 6
                                        on the verso.</layout>
                                </layoutDesc>
                            </objectDesc>

                            <handDesc>
                                <handNote scope="major" xml:id="hand-1">
                                    <p>This text was copied in a <term type="script">slanting ogival
                                            majuscule</term> script. No diacritics are visible on
                                        the surviving letters.</p>
                                </handNote>
                            </handDesc>
                        </physDesc>

                        <history>
                            <origin>The copying of the original manuscript has been dated to the
                                    <origDate calendar="gregorian" notAfter="0799" notBefore="0600">7th or 8th century</origDate>. Tchernetska ('CUL Add. 1879.5')
                                argues on the basis of the syle of script that it was copied in
                                <origPlace key="place_g7004540" ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7004540">Palestine</origPlace>.</origin>
                        </history>
                    </msPart>

